I love spending time with my family. We play together and have fun. We also talk and share stories.
When I feel upset, I sit quietly and breathe deeply to feel better. It helps me calm my mind.
I wake up, brush my teeth, and eat breakfast every morning. After that, I get dressed and start my day.
I ask for help when I need it. It is okay to ask. Asking makes things easier for me.
I play games with my friends. We have fun together. Sometimes, we play outside in the yard.
I feel happy when I see my friends. We laugh and play. We always find something fun to do.
I wash my hands before eating to stay clean. I also wash them after playing outside.
I take breaks when I feel tired. It helps me feel better. I rest for a few minutes to recharge.

column3: Spending Time with Family at Home
column4: My family and I cook dinner together. We talk and enjoy it. We also clean up together after.
When I feel nervous, I talk to my mom. She helps me feel calm. I take deep breaths too.
I listen carefully when people talk to me. It helps me understand. I try not to interrupt when they speak.
I talk to someone when I have a problem. It helps me feel better. Talking makes me feel supported.
When I feel sad, I talk to my family. It makes me feel better. They listen and help me feel happy again.
We watch movies together as a family. It is  fun and relaxing. After, we talk about our favorite parts.
I say please and thank you. It is polite and kind. I always remember to say sorry when I make a mistake.
In the evening, I brush my teeth and put on pajamas. I also pick out a book for bedtime.
I tell my family when I do something good. They cheer for me. I feel proud of myself when they do.
We celebrate together during holidays. We eat and have fun. Sometimes we give each other presents.
I smile and say hello when I meet new people. It helps me make new friends.
I build things with my toys. I use my imagination. Sometimes, I make castles or houses.
I go outside to play. I enjoy the fresh air. I like running and jumping around in the yard.
I speak clearly so others can understand me. I try to slow down when I talk.
I make my bed in the morning. It keeps my room tidy. I feel good when my room is clean.
I spend time with my friends after school. We play together. Sometimes, we draw pictures or play games.
I ask for snacks politely. I say please and thank you. I wait patiently for my turn.
